Colour pattern . Body ground colour whitish-semitransparent; bright red chromatophores occupying most of carapace surface, except for frontal and post-frontal areas; abdomen, chelipeds, second to fifth pereiopods, pleopods and tail fan whitish; gonads yellow (note: carapace bright red immediately after capture due to expansion of chromatophores, after their contraction red colour less intense) (
Fig. 3
).
